<div id="thePage:theForm:editBlock:domainAuthSection"><div class="pbSubheader brandTertiaryBgr tertiaryPalette"><h3>Email Domain Verification</h3></div><div class="pbSubsection"><table class="detailList" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tbody><tr><td class="data2Col  first " colspan="2">Salesforce requires domain-level and user-level email verification. Salesforce can send email on behalf of your users only when both levels of verification are complete. <a target="_blank" href="https://help.salesforce.com/s/articleView?id=xcloud.security_email_verification_requirements.htm&amp;type=5">Learn More</a></td></tr><tr><td class="data2Col " colspan="2"><input id="thePage:theForm:editBlock:domainAuthSection:substituteEmailDomain:cbSubstituteEmailDomain" type="checkbox" name="thePage:theForm:editBlock:domainAuthSection:substituteEmailDomain:cbSubstituteEmailDomain" checked="checked" onclick="                                                 var notificationPanel1 = document.getElementById(domainAuthEmailNotificationPanel1Id);                                                 var notificationPanel2 = document.getElementById(domainAuthEmailNotificationPanel2Id);                                                 if (document.getElementById(cbSubstituteEmailDomainId).checked) {                                                     notificationPanel1.style.display = 'none';                                                     notificationPanel2.style.display = 'none';                                                 } else {                                                     notificationPanel1.style.display = '';                                                     notificationPanel2.style.display = '';                                                 };                                                 " title="Use a substitute email address for unverified domains">
                                                Use a substitute email address for unverified domains
                        <div class="mouseOverInfoOuter" onfocus="addMouseOver(this)" onmouseover="addMouseOver(this)"><img src="/s.gif" alt="" title="" class="infoIcon">
                            <div class="mouseOverInfo" style="display: none;">
                                Enable users with unverified email domains to send user-authored emails. Salesforce sends these emails with email@{UniqueId}.sfcustomeremail.com as the From address.
                            </div>
                        </div></td></tr><tr><td class="data2Col " colspan="2"><span id="thePage:theForm:editBlock:domainAuthSection:domainAuthEmailNotificationSectionDescription:domainAuthEmailNotificationPanel1" style="display: none;"><img src="/s.gif" height="16" width="21">In February 2026, Salesforce generated a temporary allowlist of email-sending domains. Unless you use a substitute email address for unverified domains, users with email addresses that use an allowlisted domain can send email from Salesforce only until email domain verification is enforced. See <a target="_blank" href="https://help.salesforce.com/s/articleView?id=005316660&amp;type=1">Mandatory Sending-Email Domain Verification Timeline</a> in Salesforce Help.</span></td></tr><tr><td class="data2Col " colspan="2"><span id="thePage:theForm:editBlock:domainAuthSection:supressEmailNotification:domainAuthEmailNotificationPanel2" style="display: none;"><img src="/s.gif" height="16" width="21"><input id="thePage:theForm:editBlock:domainAuthSection:supressEmailNotification:cbSupressEmailNotification" type="checkbox" name="thePage:theForm:editBlock:domainAuthSection:supressEmailNotification:cbSupressEmailNotification" title="Turn off user emails for temporarily allowlisted email domains">
                                                    Turn off user emails for temporarily allowlisted email domains
                            <div class="mouseOverInfoOuter" onfocus="addMouseOver(this)" onmouseover="addMouseOver(this)"><img src="/s.gif" alt="" title="" class="infoIcon">
                                <div class="mouseOverInfo" style="display: none;">
                                    Turn off email notifications to users with temporarily allowlisted email domains. These notifications warn users that delivery can fail for future email sent from Salesforce. If you use a substitute email address for unverified domains, those notifications don't apply.
                                </div>
                            </div></span></td></tr><tr><td class="data2Col " colspan="2">Check whether your email-sending domain is verified.</td></tr><tr><th class="labelCol vfLabelColTextWrap " scope="row"><label for="thePage:theForm:editBlock:domainAuthSection:domainAuthInput:domainAuthDomain">

                        Domain Name</label></th><td class="data2Col "><input id="thePage:theForm:editBlock:domainAuthSection:domainAuthInput:domainAuthDomain" type="text" name="thePage:theForm:editBlock:domainAuthSection:domainAuthInput:domainAuthDomain" maxlength="256" size="50" title="Domain Name">
                        &nbsp;<input class="btn btn" id="thePage:theForm:editBlock:domainAuthSection:domainAuthInput:checkDomainAuthBtn" name="thePage:theForm:editBlock:domainAuthSection:domainAuthInput:checkDomainAuthBtn" onclick="A4J.AJAX.Submit('thePage:theForm',event,{'similarityGroupingId':'thePage:theForm:editBlock:domainAuthSection:domainAuthInput:checkDomainAuthBtn','parameters':{'thePage:theForm:editBlock:domainAuthSection:domainAuthInput:checkDomainAuthBtn':'thePage:theForm:editBlock:domainAuthSection:domainAuthInput:checkDomainAuthBtn'} } );return false;" value="Check Verification" type="button"></td></tr><tr><td class="data2Col  last " colspan="2"><span id="thePage:theForm:editBlock:domainAuthSection:domainAuthResults"></span></td></tr></tbody></table></div></div>